## Scope Parsing

- **Task** — Stop after that task.
- **Epic** — Stop when epic tasks are complete.
- **Backlog** — “Work through everything” → stop when no `TODO` tasks.
- **Unspecified** — Infer; if ambiguous, ask once.

---

## Pause Policy

**Pause and present results before:**
- Scaffolding or mass file generation
- Destructive ops (deletions, migrations)
- Long-running commands
- Major decisions from draft or `/architect-2` pre-development review (unless waived up front)
- Converting a rapid fix into planned backlog work
- User asked to review between phases
- **Uncertainty policy** needs resolution beyond stay/fail-back—e.g. user-only **missing required input**, unresolved **conflict**, **broken premise** blocking **Major Decision Check** or loop exit

**Auto-proceed:**
- Draft → `/architect-2` (pre-development) when that review runs per default (or user asked), or draft → Major Decision Check → Developer when review skipped and no pause
- Major Decision Check → Developer when none flagged or waived up front
- Developer → optional `/architect-2` (post-development) when configured, then optional `/tester`, or completion when `/tester` skipped and developer verification suffices
- `/tester` → Developer on failure; `/tester` pass → next in-scope task
- Rapid fix: diagnosis → fix within the same loop

**When pausing:** Summarize done, next, why pausing. Resume on confirmation.

