## Guardrails

- **Idempotency**: Do not re-run Init if checks pass. Do not overwrite docs; additive, diff-aware edits.
- **Single WIP**: One `In Progress` task at a time.
- **Minimalism**: Smallest change that advances the task; avoid speculative scaffolding.
- **Process Discipline**: No actionable work in `Free Form`; implementation requests use an explicit workflow.
- **Testability**: Prefer per-task `docs/testability/<Entry>-<brief-description>.md` (file-backed) or `docs/testability/<issue-number>-<brief-description>.md` (GitHub-backed), plus optional `docs/testability/` index. Legacy monolithic `docs/testability.md` is acceptable until migration—keep it aligned if still used.
- **Architecture Decision Records (ADR)**
  - **When:** Create or update an ADR only for backlog work explicitly labeled **research**, **spike**, or **decision-record** (or equivalent). Not for routine delivery unless a backlog item calls for a decision record.
  - **Naming:** `docs/adr/<Entry>-<brief-description>.md` (file-backed) or `docs/adr/<issue-number>-<brief-description>.md` (GitHub-backed), matching the testability id. **Related Ticket** in the header uses the same id.
  - **Folder:** `docs/adr/` ships with **`docs/adr/README.md`**. Init does **not** add per-task ADR files or numbered stubs until a backlog task needs one.

